2011 Summer New Collection RIO NEON by Harmony Gelish UV Soak Off - Tiki Tiki Laranga # 475
Gelish .5 Base & Top Coat Gel SET Harmony Nail Salon UV Manicure Polish Soak Off
description:
This wonderful set of Base and Top Coat gel provides the basics for any style of manicure or pedicure.

Gelish Foundation Base Gel creates the adhesive bond between the nail plate and gel products. This product secures adhesion while not damaging the natural nail plate. Foundation will work with Hand & Nail Harmony Gelish products as a base for Soak Off Gel Polish. Gelish Foudation cures in 10 seconds in a LED Light or 30 seconds in an UV Light.

Gelish Top It Off Gel is a sealer top gel designed to create the ultimate finish with your Gelish Soak Off Polish. It creates a high shine that will not dull, chip or peel. Top It Off is a soak off product that can quickly be removed with Soak Off Gel Remover. This coat cures in 30 seconds in a LED Light or 2 minutes in a UV Light.

title: Harmony Gelish Sizzling Summer Nights Collection - Big City Siren .5 oz.
description: 1. Sanitize, prep, and push back cuticles. Then wipe with Hand and Nail Harmony Cleanser using a lint-free wipe. Apply Hand & Nail Harmony PH Bond. 2. Apply Gelish Foundation Gel in a thin application and seal the edge of the nail. 3. Place hand in the LED light for 10 seconds or 1 minute in a UV light. 4. Lightly remove residue from the nail with a clean gel brush. 5. Apply Gelish color of choice in a thin application from cuticle to free edge. Be sure to seal the edges of the nail. 6. Place hand in LED light for 30 seconds or 2 minutes in a UV lamp. For darker coverage repeat steps 5 and 6. 7. Apply Gelish Top It Off Top Coat Sealer from cuticle to free edge using a light application. 8. Place hand in the LED light for 30 seconds or 2 minutes in a UV light. 9. Wipe off the Tacky layer with Hand & Nail Harmony Cleanser. Cure Time: - FOUNDATION GEL 10 SECONDS 1 MINUTE - STRUCTURE GEL 30 SECONDS 2 MINUTES - TOP IT OFF GEL 20-30 SECONDS 2 MINUTES - COLORS 20-30 SECONDS 2 MINUTES
